[1] Diarrhea - Nepal
Date: Tue, 27 Jul 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org> and Luiz Jacintho da Silva
<luiz_jacintho@uol.com.br>
Source: Canada.com [edited]
<http://www.canada.com/health/story.html?id=dde95622-ce3e-4df0-bfe1-e7385deeea51>

Stomach flu in Nepal kills up to 177, sickens more than 12 000 since April
--------------------------------------------------
A stomach flu in Nepal has killed up to 177 people and sickened more
than 12 000 since Apr 2004, mostly residents in remote villages with
no access to modern medicine, health officials said Tue, 27 Jul 2004.
Gastroenteritis has affected 22 districts across the Himalayan
kingdom, the Department of Epidemiology and Disease Control said.
Symptoms of the waterborne disease include fever, nausea, cramps,
abdominal pain and diarrhea. The department said most of those killed
by the disease lived in remote mountainous districts, where there is
no access to modern medicine and villagers often rely on traditional
faith healers. Villagers can spend days or even weeks walking to the
nearest town with a doctor or health clinic.
Heavy rainfall in recent weeks has also made it difficult for people
to travel. Roads and trails in many areas have been either washed
away or blocked by landslides.
The Health Ministry said doctors and medicines have been sent to most
districts affected by the disease.
