[2] Diarrhea & Cholera - Philippines (Pangasinan)
Date: Fri, 30 Jul 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: ABS-CBN news [edited]
<http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/FlashNewsStory.aspx?FlashOID=18936>

DOH reports 400 new cholera cases in Pangasinan
---------------------------------------------------
400 new cases of acute gastroenteritis have been reported in
Pangasinan by the Department of Health (DOH) in a span of 8 days, it
was learned on Fri, 30 Jul 2004.
According to DOH's surveillance and outbreak response task force, a
total of 3284 cases of acute gastroenteritis were recorded since 19
Jul 2004. In 8 days, an additional 425 cases have been recorded.
DOH epidemiologist Dr. Revelyn Cayabyab said the DOH is also
monitoring the towns of Lingayen, Bugallon, Sta. Barbara and
Bayambang for a possible clustering of cholera cases.
Cayabyab said the DOH has listed 131 cholera cases in the province
since May 2004.
[It may be that these are all cases of cholera, as the title states. - Mod.LL]
